runs.comm: back of a length and Warner pushes to mid on where Vettori's presence prevents the single
superb delivery swinging away from Warner and he plays and misses
good length but chipped back over the bowlers' head. He didn't quite time it well enough and it stops just inside the rope
back of a length and Watson is in behind it and defending back to the bowler
fuller on off stump and he drives off the inside edge to mid wicket
decent length but too straight and Warner picks it up over square leg for half a dozen!
full on middle stump and he drives powerfully to mid on
good length but a fraction too straight and he pulls past Brendon McCullum through mid wicket for four
full again and he plays a nice lofted drive over mid on which bounces just short of the ropes for four
good length but just enough width for Watson to free his arms and hit through extra cover for four. Outstanding stroke on the up!
slower ball and Watson hits it high over mid off, Oram moves backwards but can't get back quickly enough to get under it and it bounces just outside of his reach
shorter this time and he pulls off the top edge over first slip for four
full and he leans back and hammers it over long on
better length and he leans back again but mistimes it back to Bond
good length on off stump and Warner steps away to leg and crunches it through cover for four. What timing from the wee man.
fuller and crunched to Guptill at point
dropped Warner tries to heave it over the leg side and it takes the edge and flies high Taylor's right at first slip, he throws out a hand but can't hold onto it
he tries to heave it over mid wicket, gets a bottom edge back onto the stumps. New Zealand strike at last
short and slow and cut to point
shortish and slow and driven to mid off
flatter this time and he looks to cut and gets a bottom edge onto the keepers pads
tossed up and Watson plays down the wrong line, it takes him on the pad and everyone goes up and Baxter agrees that it is fairly adjacent
flatter and Johnson moves back and works it into the leg side
tossed up and Clarke uses his feet and defends back to Vettori. Clarke just has so much time
back of a length and Johnson pushes back down the track
Bond strikes again! Good length and Johnson stays crease bound looking to drive, it takes the inside edge and back onto the stumps. The promotion hasn't quite worked.
well wide down the leg side
short and Hussey 'gives himself room' and plays to point
back of a length on middle and Hussey is back and defending
good length lofted over cover and the fieldsmen do well in tandem to save the boundary
good length on middle stump and Clarke defends into the off side
flat this time and played off the back foot to point
angled into the stumps from around the wicket and Hussey closes the face and it takes the outside edge and bounces in front of backward point
flatter again and Hussey defends into the off side
tossed up and Hussey uses the crease well to cut to point where Nathan McCullum misfields
tossed up and worked into the leg side for a quick single
short and pulled out to deep forward square for a couple as Ingram misfields
full and Clarke mistimes the drive off the outside edge to backward point
good length on off and driven off the inside half of the blade to mid on
short and pulled over mid wicket for a couple to Ingram, the leg side sweeper
half volley cracked over mid off for four, super stroke
good channel from Tuffey and Hussey pushes to point where Nathan McCullum misfields
good length and Clarke plays it through mid wicket to Ingram, sweeping on the leg side
slower ball bouncer and Clarke pulls off the glove but it bounces just short of keeper Hopkins
good length worked into the leg side and mid wicket dives to save a run
back of a length whipped off his hip to square leg for a single
good channel but just enough width to guide to third man
short and pulled strongly through mid wicket past the hands of Taylor for four. Elegant stroke
played and missed outside the off stump
short and pulled behind square to the sweeper
flat again and punched off the back shoe to long on
short and pulled again through square leg for a couple right on the fence
full and driven sweetly to long on
tossed up, Clarke comes down the pitch and drives to long on
short and cut to Franklin who dives at point to save four
back of a length and pushed into the off side for an easy single
short and pulled sweetly over mid wicket. It bounces just inside the rope.

short agai and pulled behind square for a couple. The throw from the deep is good. Hopkins takes the ball in front of the stumps and whips off the bails. Hussey is found to be home safe. The question is - would it have hit the stumps if Hopkins hadn't taken it in front?
driven firmly to mid off
good length and guided to third man
bouncer down leg and called wide
good length worked into the leg side for a single
goes back to a fuller one and defends into the off side
tossed up and Hussey lofts it over mid off gloriously for four
short and pulled through backward square leg to the leg side sweeper, Tuffey, who misfields diving at full stretch
this one is slower but short and pulled behind square leg for four, beating Oram at fine leg
moves back and guides to backward point
uses his feet and drives back to the bowler who throws it back and hits Clarke on the back of the leg
short and cut to the off side sweeper
short again and cut to short cover
Clarke uses his feet and it angles dow leg, it yorks Hopkins and he misses a difficult stumping
advances down the track again (what confidence!) and drives to long off
short and pulled to deep mid wicket
short and cut to cover
comes down the track again and pushes to long on
back of a length in at the body and whipped off his hip to fine leg
back of a length and defended into the off side
short in at the body and Hussey is back and fending into the leg side
yorker played to cover
angled down the leg side. Bond just falling over slightly in his action
once again down the leg side. An action replay from the ball before
short and in at the body and Clarke works it into the leg side with soft hands
slightly slower from Bond this time and Hussey drives it straight back over his head. He doesn't quite time it well enough to get four
tossed up and Hussey tries to cut but misses
flatter and pushed into the off side as Clarke sends him back
short and played to short third man
shortish and cut hard to deep point
full and angled into leg and pushed to long on
half volley pushed to long off
half volley chipped straight to Guptill at cover. Disappointed finish to a good innings from Hussey.
yorker pushed into the covers
full and driven to long on
comes down the track and works it to mid on and he takes a well judged single
short and cut off the bottom edge into the ground and over the keeper
flatter and driven off the inside edge to mid wicket
too straight and worked through the leg side to the sweeper
tossed up and pushed back along the pitch
tossed up again and White lofts it nicely over the bowlers' head for four. Nice stroke
flatter this time and he tries to elevate again but doesn't quite get it and it bounces in front of mid off
driven firmly to mid off
tossed up and White launches it straight bakc over the bowlers' head for a maximum and that's the game. Well played Australia.
